# CSS Architecture

## Directory Structure

```
static/css/
├── base/
│   ├── variables.css    CSS custom properties (colors, spacing, typography)
│   ├── reset.css        Minimal reset + base element styles
│   └── utilities.css    Utility classes (container, spacing, flex, text)
├── components/
│   ├── buttons.css      Button variants (.btn, .btn-primary, .btn-secondary)
│   ├── forms.css        Form groups, inputs, field errors
│   └── alerts.css       Alert/flash message styles
├── layout/
│   ├── header.css       Header bar + navigation
│   └── footer.css       Footer
└── pages/
    └── home.css         Home page specific styles
```

## Adding Styles

### New component
1. Create `static/css/components/<name>.css`
2. Add `<link>` in `internal/web/components/layout.templ`

### New page
1. Create `static/css/pages/<name>.css`
2. Add `<link>` in the page's templ component or layout

## Design System

All values come from CSS custom properties in `variables.css`:

- **Colors**: `--color-primary`, `--color-error`, etc.
- **Spacing**: `--space-xs` through `--space-2xl`
- **Typography**: `--font-sans`, `--font-size-sm` through `--font-size-3xl`
- **Borders**: `--border-color`, `--border-radius`

Prefer using variables over hard-coded values. Add new variables when a value
is used more than twice.

## Button Variants

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>
<a href="/cancel" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</a>
<button class="btn btn-danger btn-sm">Delete</button>
```

## Form Pattern

```html
<div class="form-group">
    <label for="email">Email</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email"/>
    <div class="field-error" id="email-error"></div>
</div>
```

## Utility Classes

- `.container` — Max-width centered content
- `.text-center`, `.text-muted`, `.text-error`
- `.mt-sm`, `.mt-md`, `.mt-lg`, `.mt-xl` — Top margin
- `.flex`, `.flex-col`, `.items-center`, `.justify-between`
- `.hidden`, `.sr-only`
